com.interpss.core.aclf
Interface AclfNetwork

All Superinterfaces:
org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAclfAreaZone, IAclfElement, IAclfNetAdjustment, IAclfNetFormMatrix, IAclfNetFunc, IAclfNetWalkThrough, IAdaptable, IEMF<AclfBus,AclfBranch>, IMultiNet<AclfBus,AclfBranch>, INet3WXfrElement, INetBranchElement<AclfBus,AclfBranch>, INetBusElement<AclfBus>, INetworkElement, NameTag, Network<AclfBus,AclfBranch>, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Subinterfaces:
AcscNetwork
All Known Implementing Classes:
AclfNetworkImpl, AcscNetworkImpl
public interface AclfNetwork
extends Network<AclfBus,AclfBranch>, IAclfNetFunc, IAclfNetWalkThrough, IAclfNetAdjustment, INet3WXfrElement, IAclfElement, IAclfAreaZone, IAclfNetFormMatrix

A representation of the model object 'Network'. AclfNetwork class is for storing network information for AC loadflow analysis.

The following features are supported:

  • Lf Data Loaded
  • Lf Converged
  • Aclf Net Adjust
  • Flow Interface Loaded
  • Dist Gen List
  • Flow Interface List
  • Special Branch List
  • Ps Xfr PControl List
  • Tap Control List
  • Remote QBus List

See Also:

markSmallZBranch

void markSmallZBranch(double threshold,
                      boolean useVisitedStatus,
                      boolean byValueOnly)
                      throws InterpssException
mark small Z branch regarding to the threshold value. Throw exception if non-line small Z branch found. If threshold = 0.0, branch code Breaker is used to decide small Z branch. If useVisitedStatus = true, bypass those branches with branch.visited = true.

Parameters:
threshold - branch z value threshold
useVisitedStatus - branch visited status could be used for protected branches.
byValueOnly - if true, the marking is solely based on branch z value.
Throws:
InterpssException
